replies.body:
To add: Karthus has been slowly nerfed by a slew of new champions that have invulnerabilities that can dodge Karthus's ult AND/OR provide invulnerability to their teammates: 

{{champion:432}} {{champion:223}} {{champion:429}} {{champion:203}} {{champion:245}} 

And of course, the age-old classic counter {{item:3157}}

Couldn't agree more. His wall was the only thing dissuading mid laners with enough burst to kill him from just rolling over him because of the threat of getting slowed under his tower. 

Another reason the decay hurts him: it becomes tougher to land Qs on a target who's movespeed is changing up. I grew used to the constant slow that Wall of Pain provided. Now I have to predict that burst of speed my opponent gets when the slow decays.

And let's be honest here, if Karthus doesn't have his wall or a Rylai's, it's very difficult to hit successive Qs on targets with boots, especially on these increasingly mobile champs Riot keeps cooking up {{champion:429}} {{champion:103}} {{champion:7}} {{champion:203}} {{champion:157}}
